textBeforeTable: Product Bulletin - No. 1064 Cisco IOS Software Release 12.1T Ordering Procedures and Platform Support Cisco IOS® Software Release 12.1T is a Major Release consolidating functionality from previous Cisco Early Deployment Releases. Cisco IOS Software Release 12.1T Ordering Procedures Images for maintenance releases of Cisco IOS Software Release 12.1T will be available through Manufacturing for new system orders and spares, and through CCO for updates. Please refer to Product Bulletin #703 for upgrade paths from pre-12.1T releases. Downloading Cisco IOS Software Release 12.1T Downloading Cisco IOS Software Release 12.1T requires an active SmartNet Contract. WWW Instructions SmartNet Contract holders as of April 28, 1998 who are registered CCO users may download Cisco IOS Release 12.1T at http://www.cisco.com. Please follow the instructions provided in the Cisco IOS 12.1T Software Upgrade Planner at http://www.cisco.com/public/library/12.1/index.shtml The Cisco IOS 12.1T Software Upgrade Planner can be found in the following path at http://www.cisco.com: Login>Software and Support>Software Center>Cisco IOS Software (under Cisco Software Products)>Cisco IOS 12.1T. FTP Instructions FTP to http://www.cisco.com and login using your CCO user ID and password. The path is: /cisco/ios/12.1T. Customers eligible for software upgrades under warranty who do not have service contracts will need to contact the TAC at 1-800-553-2447 or, by email, at tac-dispatch@cisco.com .
